Description:
  This generator creates a new video entry in videos.yml for an unpublished talk.
  It will create the file if one does not exist, and update a talk if the id matches.

  If you do not have data for a value, omit the parameter.
  The generator will always produce a valid entry with default values for missing parameters.

Example: |
  bin/rails generate talk --event blue-ridge-ruby-2026 --title "Your first open-source contribution" --speaker "Rachael Wright-Munn"

  This will create:
      data/blue-ridge-ruby/blue-ridge-ruby-2026/videos.yml

  bin/rails g talk --event ruby-community-conference-winter-edition-2026 --speaker "Chris Hasiński" --title "Doom" --kind lightning_talk

  This will create a lightning talk entry for Chris Hasiński's talk "Doom":
      data/ruby-community-conference/ruby-community-conference-winter-edition-2026/videos.yml